  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Ship Management Operations Manager",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p><ul><li>Oversee the day-to-day operations of managed vessels, ensuring safety and efficiency that is compliant with the applicable regulations</li><li>Ensure compliance of IMO, Flag, Class, ISM, ISPS and MLC requirements</li><li>Work closely with technical teams to coordinate vessel maintenance, repairs and dry-docking activities</li><li>Monitor vessel performance, safety standards and operational KPIs</li><li>Oversee crew planning and management, including certification compliance and performance monitoring</li><li>Manage operational budgets and vessel operating expenses (OPEX) to ensure cost efficiency</li><li>Act as the main point of contact for ship owners and key stakeholders</li><li>Lead incident response, audits and inspections to enhance operational efficiency and continuous improvement</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>At least 5 years of work experience in shipping industry</li><li>At least 5 years of work experience in ship management operations including crew planning</li><li>Strong knowledge of maritime regulations and compliance requirements, including IMO, Flag, Class, ISM, ISPS and MLC </li><li>Prior experience in handling incident response, audits, and inspections</li><li>Prior experience in managing operational budgets and vessel operating expenses (OPEX)</li><li>Strong knowledge and experience of Planned Maintenance System (PMS)</li><li>Excellent problem-solving and decision-making skills</li><li>Excellent leadership and communication skills</li></ul>",
